3195
02:04:29,650 --> 02:04:30,810
That happened only once.

3196
02:04:31,150 --> 02:04:33,150
You don't get to do statistics on it.

3197
02:04:33,150 --> 02:04:38,370
There's only one sample that you can draw out

3198
02:04:38,370 --> 02:04:42,030
which is a fluctuation which took place on large scale.

3199
02:04:42,630 --> 02:04:46,050
So this is said to be cosmic variance constrained,

3200
02:04:47,630 --> 02:04:50,630
which simply means that you don't get to do statistics

3201
02:04:50,630 --> 02:04:53,570
on these large-scale variations.

3202
02:04:54,650 --> 02:04:55,390
Of course,

3203
02:04:55,390 --> 02:04:57,590
